The '''Darkwalkers''' were one of the many criminal gangs that infested [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==History==
By the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the Darkwalkers were considered by the [[RSF Intelligence Division]] as one of the four major criminal groups on Naboo, along with the [[Skaak Tippers]], the [[Nal Raka Criminal Empire]] and the [[Mummers]].<ref name="SWG:TtCotFMCG" /> The Darkwalkers had hostile relationships with Borvo's organization<ref name="SWG:EHB">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Everyone Hates Borvo|Naboo}}</ref> and the Skaak Tippers.<ref name="SWG:DDD" />

After the Battle of Yavin, the Darkwalkers kidnapped [[Karl Eckener]] because of gambling debts.<ref name="SWG:RKE" /> However, Eckener was indebted to the Darkwalkers and the Skaak Tippers and both criminal groups blackmailed Karl Eckener's father, [[Hugo Eckener/Legends|Hugo Eckener]].<ref name="SWG:EHB" /> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> they forced Hugo Eckener to hire spacers in order to attack [[Borvo Bunker]].<ref name="SWG:EHB" /> The Darkwalker [[Adjutant/Legends|adjutant]] [[Jorgellansel]] later ordered them to attack the [[Skaak Tipper Compound]]<ref name="SWG:DDD">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Doing Darkwalker Deeds|Naboo}}</ref> while the Skaak Tipper [[Toff Henrou]] ordered the spacers to attack the [[Darkwalker Cave (Theed)|Darkwalker Cave]].<ref name="SWG:DSTDW">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Doing Skaak Tipper Dirty Work|Naboo}}</ref> Nevertheless, Karl Eckener was never freed by the criminals. Hugo Eckener requested [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|RSF]] agents to [[Rescue of Karl Eckener|liberate]] his son by force. [[Bloodlord]] [[Marcus Gaw]], aegis guard [[Solon Gaw]] and [[underlord]] [[Critolus Masse]] were killed during the assault and Karl Eckener was freed.<ref name="SWG:RKE" />

Later, the Darkwalkers shot down a [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] near [[Dee'ja Peak/Legends|Dee'ja Peak]] in order to steal a [[Bioscan/Legends|bio-scanner]]. The shuttle crashed in the [[Gallo Mountains/Legends|Gallo Mountains]] and the Darkwalkers plundered the wreckage.<ref name="SWG:FowtDtftCS">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Find out what the Darkwalkers took from the Crashed Shuttle|Naboo}}</ref> Their objective was to use the bio-scanner to make a [[Bomb/Legends|bomb]] that would remain inert until its target with the programmed bio-signature came nearby. A spacer working with the scientist [[Tanoa Vills]] then raided the [[Darkwalker Cave (Dee'ja Peak)|Darkwalker Cave]] nearby to recover the stolen bio-scanner. Bloodlord [[Trienial]] and [[Chief Scientist/Legends|Chief of Science]] [[Flangolial]] were killed during the assault.<ref name="SWG:RtsBS" />

[[Boss/Legends|Boss]] [[Rugor Nass/Legends|Rugor Nass]] later sent a spacer to recover a [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] artifact that the Darkwalkers had stolen. The spacer killed the Darkwalker Bloodlord [[Vran Tristen]] in the [[Darkwalker Bunker]] and recovered the artifact.<ref name="SWG:RtGAsbtD" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Darkwalkers appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:TtCotFMCG" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> The Darkwalkers were added to the game as part of the "[[W:c:swg:Legacy Quest|Legacy Quest]],"<ref name="SWG:TtCotFMCG" /> released with the "[[W:c:swg:Publish 25 Notes for November 15, 2005|Publish 25]]," a.k.a. the "[[W:c:swg:New Game Enhancements|New Game Enhancements]]," on [[November 15]], [[2005]].<ref name="SonyCite-Publish Archive 2005">{{SonyCite|url=players/content.vm?id=64886&resource=publish|text=Publish Archive 2005}}</ref>

